{
  "Introduction": "A service catalog (or catalogue), is an organized and curated collection of business and information technology services within an enterprise. Service catalogs are knowledge management tools which designate subject matter experts (SMEs) who answer questions and requests related to the listed service. Services in the catalog are usually very repeatable and have controlled inputs, outputs, and procedures.",
  "Identifiers": [
       {
            "group_name": "\b(?i)[a-z]{4}.group\b",
            "description": "A group name is four  case insensitive letters followed by a .group extension."
            },
            {
            "device_id": "\b(?i)SN\\d{7}\b",
            "description": "A device ID is a serial number designated by 7 numbers preceded by two case insensitive letters of SN, short for serial number."
            }
  ],
"Request Categories": [
  {
       "RCC386": {
         "description": "User needs to return or hand in their old pc or computer.",
         "restriction": "The computer's or other device's serial number is required in order to complete the return."
       },
       "RCP109": {
         "description": "User is reporting a positive test for Covid."
       },
       "AUG456": {
         "description": "User wants to add users to an email group.",
         "restriction": "The group name is required in order to add users."
       },
       "RAF624": {
         "description": "User is referring a colleague for a job opportunity."
       },
       "DDL987": {
         "description": "User wants to delete an email distribution list.",
         "restriction": "The group name is required in order to delete it."
       },
       "OSL874": {
         "description": "User has a request for installing or ordering software.",
         "restriction": "In order to complete a request for installing software, a computer's or other device's serial number is required."
       }
     }
]
}

User request:

“I need to talk to HR about my lack of a computer.  I have been working here for over a month and still haven’t received my equipment.  I am ready to quit at this point.”

For the preceding request, identify all request categories and identifiers required to fulfill the users needs. All request fulfillments should be in json structure. Here is an example of the expected format.

{
  "Request_Category": {
  "serialNumber": "SN1234567"
  }
}


If no categories are applicable, the entire json should be as follows:

{}
